# AgroMind AI — Complete Local Dev Environment Setup Plan

Full local setup for AgroMind AI on Windows 11. All services run locally, no cloud needed.

---

## Section 1 — n8n Installation & Configuration

### Commands
```powershell
# Install n8n globally
npm install -g n8n

# Install pm2 globally (process manager for auto-start)
npm install -g pm2
npm install -g pm2-windows-startup

# Set environment variables (add to Windows System Environment or .env)
# Run these in PowerShell as one-time setup:
[System.Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable("N8N_PORT","5678","Machine")
[System.Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable("N8N_BASIC_AUTH_ACTIVE","false","Machine")
[System.Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable("WEBHOOK_URL","http://localhost:5678","Machine")

# Start n8n via pm2
pm2 start n8n --name agromind-n8n

# Make pm2 survive reboots
pm2-startup install
pm2 save
```

> **Note**: `pm2-windows-startup` registers pm2 as a Windows startup task. After running `pm2-startup install`, close and reopen PowerShell, then run `pm2 save`.

